                        <h1>Fuel Efficiency</h1>
                        <p xmlns="">While performance is the key factor in motorsport, fuel efficiency is very much at the heart of a modern racing car&rsquo;s design. The process of creating a fuel efficient race car is dependent on designing a lubrication package that can optimise the efficiency of the car&rsquo;s drivetrain.</p>

                        <p xmlns="">Advanced Mobil 1&trade; engine oils and gearbox lubricants are designed to reduce friction losses in the engine, transmission and differential. This allows the race team to either harness the extra power to go faster, or to help conserve fuel without compromising overall race speed and avoiding the lap time disadvantage for carrying excess fuel mass in the car.</p>

                        <p xmlns="">A fuel efficient car is especially critical at Le Mans, the toughest endurance test of them all. If the car does not have to carry extra fuel, it doesn&rsquo;t have to carry that excess mass. It&rsquo;s faster, it&rsquo;s more efficient and that&rsquo;s part of the winning package. Better lubricants equal better fuel economy, meaning championship winning performances.</p>
